Package: WienR
Version: 0.1-5
Title: Derivatives of the Wiener diffusion density and cumulative distribution function
Authors@R: c(person("Raphael", "Hartmann", email = "raphael.hartmann@protonmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
             person("Karl C.", "Klauer", email="christoph.klauer@psychologie.uni-freiburg.de", role=c("cph", "aut", "ctb", "ths")),
             person("Jean M.", "Linhart", email="jlinhart@stata.com", role=c("ctb")))
Author: Raphael Hartmann [aut, cre],
  Karl C. Klauer [cph, aut, ctb, ths],
  Jean M. Linhart [ctb]
Maintainer: Raphael Hartmann <raphael.hartmann@protonmail.com>
Depends: R (>= 4.0.0)
NeedsCompilation: yes
Description: Calculate the partial derivative of the Wiener diffusion probability density (PDF) oder cumulative distribution function (CDF)
		with respect to the relative starting point w, the upper bound a, the drift rate v, and the first-passage time t (only for PDF).
		In addition the PDF and CDF themselves are also provided. All calculations are done by using the logarithm, which makes it more stable.
